# Restart portal container after server.js changes

`portal/server.js` is bind-mounted into the `agent-portal` Docker container. Node.js does **not** hot-reload — the running process must be restarted to pick up any changes.

After finishing edits to `portal/server.js`, always run:

```bash
docker compose restart agent-portal
```

Then verify the new routes are live (should return 401, not 302):

```bash
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://localhost:3090/api/health
```

Do **not** mark the task complete until the container has been restarted.
